The total number of bodies recovered at a Malvern home outside Durban has risen to seven as paramedics recover the body of the three missing family members. This brings the total to seven people who have died in the home following the collapse of their home during the floods. Rescue-care emergency services spokesperson Garrith Jamieson says two children and one adult female have been found. “Rescue paramedics are back on the scene on Ellen Road in the Queensburgh area where the search resumed for the three missing people. Unfortunately all three have been recovered. Them being two children and one female adult so that bring the total to seven people who had passed away in this address four children and three adults. SAPS is on scene and doing the necessary and will be investigating this incident.” WATCH RELATED VIDEO BELOW: 